<subSubSection pageId="171" pageNumber="774" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="171.[2058,2651,802,1230]" pageId="171" pageNumber="774">
Genus 
<taxonomicName box="[2160,2307,921,955]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Micaelamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="171" pageNumber="774" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Micaelamys</taxonomicName>
was previously included in 
<taxonomicName box="[2103,2222,969,994]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Aethomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="171" pageNumber="774" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aethomys</taxonomicName>
, but chromosomal, morphological, and molecular data support its recognition as a distinct genus. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="171" pageNumber="774" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6887964" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6887964" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6887964/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="774" startId="171.[2058,2231,1087,1112]" targetBox="[1444,2034,813,1226]" targetPageId="171">
<paragraph blockId="171.[2058,2651,802,1230]" pageId="171" pageNumber="774">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2058,2235,1087,1112]" pageId="171" pageNumber="774">Distribution.</emphasis>
South Africa, where it is restricted to parts of the Northern, Western and Eastern Cape provinces.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="171" pageNumber="774" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="171.[2058,2651,802,1230]" box="[2058,2648,1196,1230]" pageId="171" pageNumber="774">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2058,2301,1196,1230]" pageId="171" pageNumber="774">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 93-125 mm,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="171.[1444,2653,1236,1821]" pageId="171" pageNumber="774">tail 96-138 mm, ear 16-20 mm, hindfoot 22-26 mm; weight 19-65 g. Fur of Grant's Rock Ratis dull yellowish brown or dark brown above, and pale gray or yellowish gray below. Tail is long (c.97-113% of head-body length), brownish black or dark reddish brown, and well haired with dark hairs that are longer attip of tail. Female has 3+2 = 5 pairs of nipples. Karyotype 2n = 32.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1445,2486,1441,1466]" pageId="171" pageNumber="774" type="biology_ecology">
